A case of armed robbery is being investigated by the Grahamstown SAPS, following an incident at a cash loan business today, Tuesday 31 January.&nbsp; Five men entered and robbed a cash loan firm in the CBD, said police spokesperson Captain Mali Govender. They tied up the victims and locked them inside and made off with an undisclosed sum of cash.&nbsp; Emergency services within neighbouring clusters were alerted, and within two hours a vehicle was pulled over by members of the K9 unit in Port &nbsp;Elizabeth. A man was arrested and a vehicle similar to the one used by the robbers was seized.